modules.description: Provides functions for reading and writing S-expressions from and to input and output channels, supporting both binary and textual formats. Operates on input_channel, output_channel, and S-exp data structures. Enables parsing of structured data from streams and serialization of data structures to external representations.

Loads S-expression files into custom types using a provided parser or conversion function, supporting both error-aware and exception-throwing variants. Works with S-expressions and user-defined types through a parser module or a conversion function. Parses configuration files or structured data files by converting S-expressions into specific domain models.
